<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>at a distance • in the distance</xh5><p> <i>at a distance—</i>1. not too near: This is where you get truly wonderful views of the Acropolis—seeing it <u>at a distance</u>, the Parthenon grows more impressive. 2. a long way away from smth. in time: Remembering this disaster <u>at a distance</u>, I now feel sure that it was not her fault.</p><p><i>in the distance—</i>far away: A sliver of an island appeared <u>in the distance</u>. The plane made a wide turn and continued its slow descent.</p> </entry>
